The graph of the rational function $\frac{p(x)}{q(x)}$ is shown below, with a horizontal asymptote of $y = 0$ and a vertical asymptote of $ x=-1 $. If $q(x)$ is quadratic, $p(2)=1$, and $q(2) = 3$, find $p(x) + q(x).$
